{{!
    @template scormreport_question/scoredbinarysection

    Creates a section with a title and a percentagecircle with its indicator set to the passed percentage and the exact numbers being displayed in the middle.
    Also shows the id as a tooltip on hover.

    Classes required for JS:
    * none

    Data attributes required for JS:
    * none

    Context variables required for this template:
    * id - The full id of the associated DB object
    * title - the title of the section
    * correct - the amount of correct answers
    * total - the total amount of answers
    * percentage - the percentage of correct answers

    Example context (json):
    {
        "id": "My debugging id",
        "title": "My scored binary section",
        "correct": 10,
        "total": 20,
        "percentage": 50,
    }

}}

<div id="scormreport_question_sectionwrapper_{{id}}">
    <div class="scormreport_question_title">
        <h2 title="{{id}}">{{title}}</h2>
        <span class="scormreport_question_rightside">{{#str}}answers, scormreport_question{{/str}}: {{answers}}</span>
    </div>
    <div id="scormreport_question_section_{{id}}" class="scormreport_question_plotly_section">
        {{<scormreport_question/percentagecircle}}
            {{$text}}{{correct}}/{{total}}{{/text}}
            {{$percentage}}{{percentage}}{{/percentage}}
        {{/scormreport_question/percentagecircle}}
    </div>
</div>